# Arc: Other | Scene: MythranArcWarrior1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah watched over her men as the last of the preparations were finished."
    new "Sarah watched over her men as the last of the preparations were finished."

    old "She was eager to leave Nauyziri behind her."
    new "She was eager to leave Nauyziri behind her."

    old "Around her, a flurry of officers, commanders, all struggling for a moment."
    new "Around her, a flurry of officers, commanders, all struggling for a moment."

    old "Sarah wondered how Vaelen had ever made it seem so easy."
    new "Sarah wondered how Vaelen had ever made it seem so easy."

    old "She had never known the meaning of the word busy before now."
    new "She had never known the meaning of the word busy before now."

    old "Lady Carolyn had discussed the last of the logistical matters with her as well."
    new "Lady Carolyn had discussed the last of the logistical matters with her as well."

    old "The mercenary company would march back to Rahayal, together with the Mythran host."
    new "The mercenary company would march back to Rahayal, together with the Mythran host."

    old "Their vast supplies and larger force would make the march back to Rahayal significantly easier."
    new "Their vast supplies and larger force would make the march back to Rahayal significantly easier."

    old "In addition, their maps were far better than any they had. Combined with skilled navigators, they were likely to be out of the desert in little time at all."
    new "In addition, their maps were far better than any they had. Combined with skilled navigators, they were likely to be out of the desert in little time at all."

    old "More requests came in during the day."
    new "More requests came in during the day."

    old "Approved. Denied. Denied. Approved."
    new "Approved. Denied. Denied. Approved."

    old "Sarah found herself signing off on the orders so fast, she sometimes struggled to recall what she had signed only a moment later."
    new "Sarah found herself signing off on the orders so fast, she sometimes struggled to recall what she had signed only a moment later."

    old "She saw Kate standing nearby."
    new "She saw Kate standing nearby."

    old "I think I'm going to need a secretary if I want to keep doing this."
    new "I think I'm going to need a secretary if I want to keep doing this."

    old "Well, I'd love to play secretary with you, but I can't read or write for shit."
    new "Well, I'd love to play secretary with you, but I can't read or write for shit."

    old "Sarah sighed. It was true."
    new "Sarah sighed. It was true."

    old "Kate had been given some benefits, growing up in the castle, but she had been taught to read and write for what a servant girl might be expected to do."
    new "Kate had been given some benefits, growing up in the castle, but she had been taught to read and write for what a servant girl might be expected to do."

    old "Order lists for kitchen supplies. Basic work instructions."
    new "Order lists for kitchen supplies. Basic work instructions."

    old "Those were a far cry from the kind of legal paperwork that Sarah struggled through."
    new "Those were a far cry from the kind of legal paperwork that Sarah struggled through."

    old "Sarah tried to imagine what options she really had. Literacy was not exactly a skill in abundance among mercenaries."
    new "Sarah tried to imagine what options she really had. Literacy was not exactly a skill in abundance among mercenaries."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah thought of the answer."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah thought of the answer."

    old "The girl couldn't swing a sword to save her life, but she'd been raised in a palace all her life."
    new "The girl couldn't swing a sword to save her life, but she'd been raised in a palace all her life."

    old "As the princess, heir to a throne she'd now lost, she would undoubtedly know how to read and write."
    new "As the princess, heir to a throne she'd now lost, she would undoubtedly know how to read and write."

    old "Samayra..."
    new "Samayra..."

    old "Ooh, I was just thinking out loud. Samayra could work as my secretary."
    new "Ooh, I was just thinking out loud. Samayra could work as my secretary."

    old "Kate raised an eyebrow."
    new "Kate raised an eyebrow."

    old "You mind if I fuck your secretary?"
    new "You mind if I fuck your secretary?"

    old "Very funny. Don't bully the girl, she's been through enough."
    new "Very funny. Don't bully the girl, she's been through enough."

    old "Hey, I never said I wouldn't make it worth her time."
    new "Hey, I never said I wouldn't make it worth her time."

    old "Sarah waved her hand at Kate, hoping to cut off whatever fun she was having."
    new "Sarah waved her hand at Kate, hoping to cut off whatever fun she was having."

    old "Enough of that, I need to focus."
    new "Enough of that, I need to focus."

    old "A moment later, soldiers pulled Kate away. Everyone seemed so busy, especially when they were almost ready to leave."
    new "A moment later, soldiers pulled Kate away. Everyone seemed so busy, especially when they were almost ready to leave."

    old "It was another frenzied hour later when Lady Carolyn arrived."
    new "It was another frenzied hour later when Lady Carolyn arrived."

    old "Your army looks in tip top shape."
    new "Your army looks in tip top shape."

    old "You've been making the rounds?"
    new "You've been making the rounds?"

    old "Reading the reports. I don't do well walking long distances in my heels."
    new "Reading the reports. I don't do well walking long distances in my heels."

    old "Have you ever considered not wearing heels when out on campaign?"
    new "Have you ever considered not wearing heels when out on campaign?"

    old "What if I happened to die on a campaign?"
    new "What if I happened to die on a campaign?"

    old "They'd find my body dressed in military rags and ugly shoes?"
    new "They'd find my body dressed in military rags and ugly shoes?"

    old "Gods, I'd rather just suffer the inconvenience."
    new "Gods, I'd rather just suffer the inconvenience."

    old "Anyway, you're right. We're almost ready to set out."
    new "Anyway, you're right. We're almost ready to set out."

    old "Good, good. Can't wait to leave this horrid place behind me."
    new "Good, good. Can't wait to leave this horrid place behind me."

    old "Sarah looked up from the paperwork."
    new "Sarah looked up from the paperwork."

    old "You dislike this place too?"
    new "You dislike this place too?"

    old "I miss the civilized world. A place like this, only the scholars can enjoy."
    new "I miss the civilized world. A place like this, only the scholars can enjoy."

    old "Sarah nodded. She imagined her own concerns to run deeper, but she was happy to realize she wasn't the only one that wanted to leave."
    new "Sarah nodded. She imagined her own concerns to run deeper, but she was happy to realize she wasn't the only one that wanted to leave."

    old "Great, then I'll issue the final orders and we can set out."
    new "Great, then I'll issue the final orders and we can set out."

    old "With that, Sarah handed off a set of instructions to the runners, whom swiftly took off to distribute the orders to each rank."
    new "With that, Sarah handed off a set of instructions to the runners, whom swiftly took off to distribute the orders to each rank."

    old "Before long, the last parts of the camp were broken down and the wagons were rigged."
    new "Before long, the last parts of the camp were broken down and the wagons were rigged."

    old "Looking out at the gathered mass of mercenaries and Mythrans, the city almost seemed alive for a moment, buzzing with people."
    new "Looking out at the gathered mass of mercenaries and Mythrans, the city almost seemed alive for a moment, buzzing with people."

    old "Soon they would be gone, and the city would be dead again. No people. No witnesses. Left only to the encroaching sands."
    new "Soon they would be gone, and the city would be dead again. No people. No witnesses. Left only to the encroaching sands."

    old "The horns rang out and the lead of the caravan began to pull out."
    new "The horns rang out and the lead of the caravan began to pull out."

    old "Slowly, each wagon pulled into motion."
    new "Slowly, each wagon pulled into motion."

    old "They were moving towards Rahayal, and all that the city promised."
    new "They were moving towards Rahayal, and all that the city promised."

